tasks.details:
Create InputHandler.gd component:
1. Extends Node
2. Enum Direction { UP, DOWN, LEFT, RIGHT }
3. Variables: current_direction, buffered_direction
4. In _input(event):
   - Check Input.is_action_just_pressed for move_up/down/left/right
   - Map to Direction enum
   - Check if new direction is opposite of current_direction (UP<->DOWN, LEFT<->RIGHT)
   - If not opposite, set buffered_direction
5. Public method consume_buffered_direction() -> Direction: returns buffered_direction, resets buffer

Pseudo-code:
```gdscript
# InputHandler.gd
extends Node
enum Direction { UP, DOWN, LEFT, RIGHT }
var current_direction = Direction.RIGHT
var buffered_direction: Variant = null

func _input(event):
    if Input.is_action_just_pressed('move_up'): _buffer_direction(Direction.UP)
    elif Input.is_action_just_pressed('move_down'): _buffer_direction(Direction.DOWN)
    elif Input.is_action_just_pressed('move_left'): _buffer_direction(Direction.LEFT)
    elif Input.is_action_just_pressed('move_right'): _buffer_direction(Direction.RIGHT)

func _buffer_direction(dir: Direction):
    if not _is_opposite(dir, current_direction):
        buffered_direction = dir

func _is_opposite(a: Direction, b: Direction) -> bool:
    return (a == Direction.UP and b == Direction.DOWN) or (a == Direction.DOWN and b == Direction.UP) or (a == Direction.LEFT and b == Direction.RIGHT) or (a == Direction.RIGHT and b == Direction.LEFT)
```
